      "side": 1,
      "message": "My 2c is that if you are looking at a cheaper alternative to Kinesis, possibly SNS+SQS in a fixed HA deployment model would work.\n\nHowever, we have users with high availability and auto-scaling; therefore, SNS+SQS won\u0027t work for them.\n\nI agree that this implementation is a good alternative, but it should be done in a separate plugin, possibly using the `DynamicItem\u003cForwarder\u003e` declared by the `high-availability` plugin and implemented by others, including `KinesisForwarder` and `SNSSQSForwarder` as two alternatives.",
